+# engine: runs doctor journal health checker
+
+## Goal
+
+Add `flowai-workflow runs doctor` so operators can diagnose one run's durable
+recovery artifacts and apply only safe mechanical repairs: removing a torn
+final journal line and clearing a stale lock for that same run.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 made `<workflow>/runs/<run-id>/journal.jsonl` the sole durable recovery
+surface. The replayer tolerates duplicate event identifiers and a malformed
+partial final line, but operators currently have no command that distinguishes
+expected crash tails from semantic corruption or cross-checks the run
+directory and lock file.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns journal paths, event replay, duplicate
+  handling, and partial-tail tolerance.
+- `src/state/state.ts` owns run and node directory path helpers.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` owns lock parsing and process liveness checks.
+- `src/cli.ts` has explicit subcommand routing and argument parsing without
+  external dependencies.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Do not write a second journal replayer; doctor must call
+  `replayRunJournal()` and inspect the replay result.
+- Do not duplicate run, node, journal, or lock path construction.
+- Do not repair semantic corruption. Repair may remove only a torn final line
+  and a stale lock for the selected run.
+- No prompts and no new dependencies.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
